      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FLASH GUCCI (7) held her own to the line last start and filled a minor placing, beaten only 1.3 lengths (21.25) behind Romani Lass at this track. Good beginner but will need a little luck early crossing from an outside draw. Must come into calculations. SLICE OF LIFE (2) shows ability but remains a maiden after six starts. Gave a huge sight last time and went down narrowly when second. Safe beginner who has drawn to advantage. Expected to be in the finish again. ZIPPING STITCH (6) freshened since a nice debut run when hitting the frame at Wentworth Park over 520m (30.82). Can find the frame again this time. LOCK STAR (5) can play a role in the finish without surprising.",
